  head
    include ../structure/head

  body.off-canvas-sidebar#articles-scrollspy  
    .page-wrapper
      include ../structure/header--off-canvas-sidebar
      include ../modules/sidebar
      main.content-wrapper
                  
        .post-title
          h1 How to add hotspots on a 360 spin
          p.post-meta
            | Created:
            span 21st August 2015  /
            | Author: 
            span Johnny Black
        hr

        +newArticle('Before you started', 'spy-before-start')
          p The bigger your original image, the more options you’ll have.
            br
            | For best results, upload images of:
          ul.success-list
            li At least 2500px width
            li if JPEG, 92% to 96% quality
          p Sirv works with any image, regardless of type, size or quality. It automatically resizes and optimizes your images according to the users device. By uploading big, high quality images, you’ll ensure that Sirv always delivers superb quality 
            a(href="#") Sirv Zooms
            |   and permit glorious clarity on hi-res screens.
          p For more tips, read 
            a(href="#") Getting started with Sirv
            |. For help, 
            a(href="#") contact Sirv support
            |  from your control panel.

          
        +newArticle('Options', 'spy-options')
          p Output your images at any size in a split second. It’s simple and each of the options are explained below. For quick reference, the 
            a(href="#") Table of Options
            |  lists all 60 options.
        
        
        +newArticle('URL format', 'spy-url-format')
          p New images are created by appending options in your image URL.
            br
            | Here is an image without any options:

          .code
            pre
              code.hljs.nohighlight //test1.sirv.com/blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg

          img(src="//test1.sirv.com/blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg" width="500" height="333" alt="blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg")
          

          p Here is the same image scaled to 300px (notice the URL):
            
          .code
            pre
              code.hljs.nohighlight //test1.sirv.com/blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg?scale.width=300

          img(src="//test1.sirv.com/blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg?scale.width=300" width="300" height="200" alt="blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg")
          
          p Pixel values are referenced using the number only. For percentage values, always use the ‘
            span.bold %
            | ‘ sign, eg: 40%.
            br
            | Here is the same image with lots more options – note that multiple parameters in the URL are separated by the ‘
            span.bold &
            | ‘ character:
                
          .code
            pre
              code.hljs.nohighlight //test1.sirv.com/blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg?scale.width=300&colortone=texas&frame.style=mirror&text.text=%C2%A9Steve%20Wilson&text.size=40%&text.color=white&text.position=northeast&text.font.family=Shadows%20Into%20Light%20Two

                
          img(src="//test1.sirv.com/blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg?scale.width=300&colortone=texas&frame.style=mirror&text.text=%C2%A9Steve%20Wilson&text.size=40%&text.color=white&text.position=northeast&text.font.family=Shadows%20Into%20Light%20Two" width="300" height="200" alt="blog-brno-harvest-kolache-032.jpg")
          
